Development Notes 

Written for Mac OSX Yosemite (10.10.3), but may be similar on Windows.

Running mongo db
1. open terminal
2. run "sudo -s" to run as root user
3. run "mongod"
4. you can run a client terminal with the "mongo" command 
	useful commands: "use whysosingle" <- switches the database
			 		 "db.users.drop()" <- deletes the collection (or table if thinking from SQL)

Running express app
1. open terminal
2. navigate to project directory
3. run "node app"
4. Open safari and go to localhost:1337